    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Gmelina arborea, having a medium texture with a straight or roey grain. It is easy to work and polishes to a silky smooth finish with a high gloss. Gmelina wood is used for furniture, cabinetry, boatbuilding, musical instruments, and decorative boxes. The tree is also cultivated for papermaking pulp. Although a common name includes the word "beech," it is not a beech.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
